  "text": "In the clinic, [CITATION_1] F-fluorodeoxyglucose ( 18 FDG) positron emission tomography is used to detect tumours and monitor their response to treatment by imaging their increased glucose uptake compared with normal tissue. In this situation, quantifying lactate potentially offers complementary information on (steadystate) lactate concentrations, particularly in organs such as the brain where the high glucose consumption and hence [CITATION_2] FDG uptake of normal tissue obscures their differentiation.",
